text: The sequence x[n]=(-1)^n is obtained by sampling the continuouse-time sinusoidal signal x(t)= cos(w0t) at 1-ms intervals, i.e.,\n\nDetermine the three smallest distinct possible values of w0 as a multiple of nx10^3 in the following format: w0 1, w0 2, w0 3, e.g 1, 2, 3
Which of the following statements regarding the rules are correct?\nMark all correct answers.

answer_options.answer_text: There will be up to 84 slots for autonomous vehicles.
The diameter of the outer circle in skidpad is 18.25m.
The DOO penalty for acceleration is 0.2s.
The vehicle must have a wheelbase of at least 1.525 m.
Until the waiting list closes, execution of A 5.4.2 is suspended and teams will no longer be de-registered.
Data logger data must be made available at latest one hour after the closing of the respective event.
The Node-ID of the RES has to be set to 0x011 at the competition.
Each ASSI must meet requirements according to T 10.11.
The load applicator used to test any panel or tube must be metallic and have a radius of 32 mm.
